title: Nintendo Cracks Down on Palworld’s Pokémon Mod - IGN Daily Fix
description:
In today's Daily Fix:
A popular mod for the hit survival/crafting game Palworld has incurred the wrath of Nintendo. The mod replaced many assets with Pokémon characters, and of course Nintendo was having none of that. Popular mod hosting site NexusMods has also begun taking down other Pokémon-esque mods for Palworld. In other news, Riot Games has laid off about 11% of the company, amounting to roughly 530 people. Riot Games CEO explained that the company is without a sharp focus and cannot sustain such a large workforce. This continues a very troubling trend of layoffs in the tech and gaming industries. And finally, Nintendo has revealed new Joy-Con colors, this time a spring pink theme to coincide with the launch of Princess Peach: Showtime later this year.

title: Palworld: How to Level Up Fast
description:
You’ll earn levels quickly in Palworld when you’re just starting out, but after you’ve got a dozen or so levels under your belt, the pace starts to slow down. Fighting the syndicate, pals, and constructing items or structures will all provide some experience benefits, but these methods aren't very quick for fast leveling. In this video, we'll show you exactly how to level up fast in Palworld.

title: Avatar: The Last Airbender Producers Reveal Secrets From New Trailer
description:

title: Hollywood Keeps Reminding Us Why We Need Physical Media More Than Ever
description:
A new year means yet another shuffling of the films and television shows available on the myriad of streaming services that customers now have to keep track of. But despite the age of digital media promising unlimited access and more options than ever, we have often seen the opposite actually happen in practice. For a pressing recent example, most of the Star Trek films were taken off of Paramount+ in the United States at the start of 2024, with only the newest trilogy of films starring Chris Pine remaining on the service. Paramount may have promised that their in-house streaming service was the place for all your Trek needs, but if you want to watch the first 10 films on streaming, you’ll have to fire up HBO Max.

title: Madame Web - Exclusive Official Behind the Scenes Clip (2024) Dakota Johnson, Sydney Sweeney
description:
"Meanwhile, in another universe…” In a switch from the typical genre, Madame Web tells the standalone origin story of one of Marvel publishing's most enigmatic heroines. The suspense-driven thriller stars Dakota Johnson as Cassandra Webb, a paramedic in Manhattan who may have clairvoyant abilities. Forced to confront revelations about her past, she forges a relationship with three young women destined for powerful futures...if they can all survive a deadly present.

The cast includes Dakota Johnson, Sydney Sweeney, Isabela Merced, Celeste O’Connor, Tahar Rahim, Mike Epps, Emma Roberts, and Adam Scott. Directed by SJ Clarkson, Madame Web opens in theaters on February 14, 2024.

#IGN #Marvel

title: Like a Dragon: Infinite Wealth Review
description:
Like a Dragon: Infinite Wealth reviewed by Tristan Ogilvie on PlayStation 5. Also available on PlayStation 4, Xbox, and PC.

"Like a Dragon: Infinite Wealth’s overhauled combat system injects some welcome flexibility and flash into every turn, its difficulty curve has been pruned of nasty spikes to remove the need for repetitive grinding we endured in the last turn-based game, and its spectacular Hawaiian setting is crammed with enough enjoyable activities to overload even the most ambitious of holiday itineraries. A compelling, country-hopping crime story kept me on the hook like a freshly lured barracuda for the 50 hours it took to complete, and the vibrant new job classes and unique combat arenas ensured that the fighting continued to feel fresh. Sprawling, enthralling, and packed with dynamic brawling, Like a Dragon: Infinite Wealth isn’t just the best turn-based Like a Dragon game, it’s one of the greatest games in the entire series."

title: Tekken 8 Review
description:
Reviewed by Ronny Barrier on PlayStation 5. Also available on Xbox Series X|S, and PC.
Tekken 8 is the newest contender in Bandai Namco's long running legacy fighter. With almost three decades of history, how can a new entry in the storied franchise make its mark? By remembering what came before, but never ceasing its strive for improvement. From new mechanics, to a much improved online experience from previous Tekkens, and a full suite of offline modes, we cover it all in this Tekken 8 review.

description:
The greater the spy, the bigger the lie.
 
From the twisted mind of Matthew Vaughn (Kingsman franchise, Kick-Ass) comes Argylle, a razor-witted, reality-bending, globe-encircling spy thriller.
 
Bryce Dallas Howard (Jurassic World franchise) is Elly Conway, the reclusive author of a series of best-selling espionage novels, whose idea of bliss is a night at home with her computer and her cat, Alfie. But when the plots of Elly’s fictional books—which center on secret agent Argylle and his mission to unravel a global spy syndicate—begin to mirror the covert actions of a real-life spy organization, quiet evenings at home become a thing of the past.

title: Palworld: Tower of the Rayne Syndicate Boss Fight (Zoe and Grizzbolt)
description:
Early on in Palworld, you'll be given the quest to take on the Tower of the Rayne Syndicate boss fight. This boss fight can be tough for a few different reasons. First, the Pal you need to fight hits hard, you can't enter the fight with any of your multiplayer friends, and there is a 10-minute timer on the whole thing. In this video, we took the boss on at level 22 and defeated her without too many issues, even without ground-element Pals.

title: The Return of Steamboat Willie - Official Teaser Trailer
description:
After 95 years of being locked away, Willie is free and he wants his Steamboat back. Check out this creepy trailer for The Return of Steamboat Willie, an upcoming new film being created in Unreal Engine by Fewture Studios. 

The Return of Steamboat Willie is written by Joe Smith. It is produced by Yonatan Hagos, Kelvin Craver, and Darron Ross. VFX is by TxREK & Henry Gonzalez. Music is by Omar Habbak and sound design is by Zac Brunson. It is directed by Kai Henry, TxREK, and Joe Smith.

title: Suicide Squad: Kill the Justice League - Official Elseworlds Overview
description:
Join members of the development team at Rocksteady for a peek at what you can expect with the post-launch content coming to Suicide Squad: Kill the Justice League, featuring seasons themed around a different DC character, and will incorporate alternate realities invaded by Brainiac known as Elseworlds. In March 2024, Season 1 will feature the arrival of The Joker, in the form of an Elseworlds twist on the iconic DC Super-Villain. This new version of The Joker will be available as a new playable character. Season 1 will also feature a new Joker-themed environment, two episodes of with new Missions, activities and strongholds, new boss fights and enemy variants, and more. The team at Rocksteady also gives a breakdown of social features and four-player cooperative mode, and more.

Suicide Squad: Kill the Justice League will be available on PlayStation 5, Xbox Series X/S, and PC on February 2, 2024.
